TITLE: Report Definition - Type Report Definition
DESCRIPTION: Describes how report definitions are handled in Visual Studio's Report Designer. The designer creates classes inheriting `Telerik.Reporting.Report`, called Type Report Definitions. These definitions (CLR, CS, or VB) can be passed to the Reporting engine via the `TypeReportSource`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/getting-started/about-telerik-reporting.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
If you design a report in the Report Designer for Visual Studio, the result is a class inheriting `Telerik.Reporting.Report`. These are the so-called __Type Report Definitions__. They may be referenced also as _CLR_ (Common Language Runtime), _CS_ (C Sharp), or _VB_ (Visual Basic) report definitions. These separate CLR types may be passed to the Reporting engine through the built-in [TypeReportSource](/api/telerik.reporting.typereportsource).
```

