TITLE: Binding ObjectDataSource to DataTable in C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# code snippet demonstrates how to create a DataTable, add a calculated field, configure an ObjectDataSource, and set up a report to use it. It also shows how to preview the report in a Windows Forms Report Viewer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-source-components/objectdatasource-component/bind-to-data-table.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
public void HowToBindToDataTable()
{
    DataTable dt = new DataTable();
    dt.Columns.Add("ProductID", typeof(int));
    dt.Columns.Add("ProductName", typeof(string));
    dt.Columns.Add("UnitPrice", typeof(decimal));
    dt.Columns.Add("UnitsInStock", typeof(Int16));
    dt.Rows.Add(1, "Chai", 18.00, 39);
    dt.Rows.Add(2, "Chang", 19.00, 17);
    dt.Rows.Add(3, "Aniseed Syrup", 10.00, 13);

    DataColumn calcColumn = new DataColumn("Total");
    calcColumn.DataType = typeof(decimal);
    calcColumn.Expression = "UnitPrice * UnitsInStock";
    dt.Columns.Add(calcColumn);

    ObjectDataSource objectDataSource = new ObjectDataSource();
    objectDataSource.DataSource = dt;

    Report report = new Report();
    report.DataSource = objectDataSource;

    ReportProcessor reportProcessor = new ReportProcessor();
    RenderingResult result = reportProcessor.RenderReport("PDF", report, null);

    System.IO.File.WriteAllBytes("report.pdf", result.DocumentBytes);
}
```

