TITLE: Implementing Custom Aggregate Function in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a custom aggregate function called 'Concatenate' in C#. It implements the IAggregateFunction interface and uses the AggregateFunctionAttribute to define the function name for use in expressions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/expressions/extending-expressions/user-aggregate-functions.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
[AggregateFunction(Name = "Concatenate")]
public class ConcatenateAggregateFunction : IAggregateFunction
{
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

    public void Accumulate(object[] values)
    {
        if (values[0] != null)
        {
            sb.Append(values[0].ToString());
        }
    }

    public void Merge(IAggregateFunction aggregateFunction)
    {
        ConcatenateAggregateFunction agg = (ConcatenateAggregateFunction)aggregateFunction;
        this.sb.Append(agg.sb.ToString());
    }

    public object GetValue()
    {
        return sb.ToString();
    }
}
```

