TITLE: Binding ObjectDataSource to BusinessObject in VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This VB.NET code snippet demonstrates creating a custom business object, configuring an ObjectDataSource, and previewing a report using the Windows Forms Report Viewer. The business object includes methods returning various data types and supports method parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-source-components/objectdatasource-component/bind-to-a-businessobject.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
<DataObject()> _
Public Class Business
    <DataObjectMethod()> _
    Public Function GetDataTable() As DataTable
        Dim table As New DataTable()
        table.Columns.Add("ID", GetType(Integer))
        table.Columns.Add("Name", GetType(String))
        table.Rows.Add(1, "John")
        table.Rows.Add(2, "Jane")
        Return table
    End Function

    <DataObjectMethod()> _
    Public Function GetPersons() As IEnumerable(Of Person)
        Return New List(Of Person) From { _
            New Person With {.ID = 1, .Name = "John"}, _
            New Person With {.ID = 2, .Name = "Jane"} _
        }
    End Function

    <DataObjectMethod()> _
    Public Function GetPersonsWithParameters(ByVal id As Integer, ByVal name As String) As IEnumerable(Of Person)
        Return New List(Of Person) From { _
            New Person With {.ID = id, .Name = name} _
        }
    End Function
End Class

Public Class Person
    Public Property ID As Integer
    Public Property Name As String
End Class

Dim report As New Report()
Dim detail As New DetailSection()
report.Items.Add(detail)

Dim objectDataSource As New ObjectDataSource()
objectDataSource.DataMember = "GetPersons"
objectDataSource.DataSource = GetType(Business)

Dim table As New Table()
Dim body As New TableBody()
table.Bodies.Add(body)

Dim row As New TableRow()
body.Rows.Add(row)

Dim cell As New TableCell()
row.Cells.Add(cell)

Dim textBox As New TextBox()
textBox.Value = "= Fields.Name"
cell.Items.Add(textBox)

detail.Items.Add(table)
report.DataSource = objectDataSource

Dim reportProcessor As New ReportProcessor()
Dim result As RenderingResult = reportProcessor.RenderReport("PDF", report, Nothing)

System.IO.File.WriteAllBytes("report.pdf", result.DocumentBytes)
```

