TITLE: Implement Send Mail Message in C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# code snippet demonstrates how to implement the SendMailMessage method in the ReportsController using MailMessage and SMTP client. It outlines the steps to configure and send emails from the Telerik Reporting REST service.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/embedding-reports/host-the-report-engine-remotely/implement-send-mail-message.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
"// Consider passing the credentials as parameters from the client
// Alternatively configure the SMTP client from the application's configuration file.
//
// smtp.Credentials = new NetworkCredential("user", "password");

using (MailMessage message = new MailMessage())
{
    message.From = new MailAddress(mailSettings.SenderEmail);

    foreach (string recipient in mailSettings.Recipients)
    {
        message.To.Add(recipient);
    }

    message.Subject = sendEmail.Subject;
    message.Body = sendEmail.Body;
    message.IsBodyHtml = true;

    if (sendEmail.Attachments != null)
    {
        foreach (string attachment in sendEmail.Attachments)
        {
            message.Attachments.Add(new Attachment(attachment));
        }
    }

    using (SmtpClient smtp = new SmtpClient(mailSettings.SmtpServer, mailSettings.Port))
    {
        smtp.EnableSsl = mailSettings.UseSsl;
        smtp.Send(message);
    }
}"
```

