TITLE: Custom Newtonsoft JSON Model Binder
DESCRIPTION: A custom model binder that uses Newtonsoft.Json to deserialize request bodies, providing an alternative to the default System.Text.Json model binding
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/knowledge-base/use-two-json-serializers-in-same-asp-net-core-project.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: CSharp
CODE:
```
public class NewtonsoftJsonModelBinder : IModelBinder 
{
	public async Task BindModelAsync(ModelBindingContext bindingContext) 
	{
		if (bindingContext == null) throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(bindingContext));

		using var reader = new StreamReader(bindingContext.HttpContext.Request.Body);

		string body = await reader.ReadToEndAsync().ConfigureAwait(continueOnCapturedContext: false);
		object? value = Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConvert.DeserializeObject(body, bindingContext.ModelType);
		bindingContext.Result = ModelBindingResult.Success(value);
	}
}
```

