TITLE: Implementing Custom Aggregate Function in VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the implementation of a custom aggregate function 'Concatenate' in VB.NET. It implements the IAggregateFunction interface and uses the AggregateFunctionAttribute to define the function name for use in expressions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/expressions/extending-expressions/user-aggregate-functions.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
<AggregateFunction(Name:="Concatenate")> _
Public Class ConcatenateAggregateFunction
    Implements IAggregateFunction
    Private sb As New StringBuilder()

    Public Sub Accumulate(ByVal values As Object()) Implements IAggregateFunction.Accumulate
        If values(0) IsNot Nothing Then
            sb.Append(values(0).ToString())
        End If
    End Sub

    Public Sub Merge(ByVal aggregateFunction As IAggregateFunction) Implements IAggregateFunction.Merge
        Dim agg As ConcatenateAggregateFunction = DirectCast(aggregateFunction, ConcatenateAggregateFunction)
        Me.sb.Append(agg.sb.ToString())
    End Sub

    Public Function GetValue() As Object Implements IAggregateFunction.GetValue
        Return sb.ToString()
    End Function
End Class
```

