TITLE: Implementing User Function for Dynamic ColorPalette in C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# function creates an IColorPalette object from a list of hex color strings. It can handle either multiple color parameters or a single string with colors separated by '#'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/knowledge-base/colorpalette-set-with-bindings.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
public static IColorPalette UserColorPalette(params string[] hexColors)
{
    string[] colors = hexColors;

    if (null == colors || colors.Length <= 0)
    {
        return null;
    }

    if (colors.Length == 1)
    {
        colors = colors[0]
            .Split('#')
            .Where(c => !string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(c))
            .Select(c => $"#{c.Trim()}")
            .ToArray();
    }

    ColorPalette colorPalette = new ColorPalette(colors);

    return colorPalette;
}
```

