TITLE: Querying SQL Data Source with Parameter
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query retrieves product data from several tables, filtering the results based on the ProductSubcategoryID parameter.  It joins Production.Product with Production.ProductSubcategory and filters by Production.Product.ProductSubcategoryID. The @ProductSubcategoryID parameter is used to dynamically filter the result set.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/report-parameters/how-to-cascade-parameters-with-applied-filtering-on-data-source-level.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
SELECT
		Production.Product.ProductNumber, Production.Product.Name AS ProductName, 
		Production.ProductSubcategory.Name AS SubcategoryName
	FROM
		Production.Product 
		INNER JOIN Production.ProductSubcategory 
			ON Production.Product.ProductSubcategoryID = Production.ProductSubcategory.ProductSubcategoryID
	WHERE
		(Production.Product.ProductSubcategoryID = @ProductSubcategoryID)
```

