TITLE: Implementing AddInSet Method in CacheStorage
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the implementation of the AddInSet method in the CacheStorage class. It handles adding a value to a set stored in the cache, with error handling for null deserialization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/knowledge-base/add-in-set-null-reference-exception.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: CSharp
CODE:
```
public void AddInSet(string key, string value)
{
	using (this.AcquireSetLock(key))
	{
		var raw = this.GetBytes(key);
		var set = null == raw ? new HashSet<string>() : SerializationUtils.Deserialize<HashSet<string>>(raw);
		if (set == null)
		{
			// Not localizable by design
			const string error = "Incorrect value (null) deserialized. Make sure you are using CacheStorage inside single-instance application deployment only.";

			System.Diagnostics.Trace.WriteLine(error);
			throw new ApplicationException(error);
		}
		set.Add(value);
		this.SetBytes(key, SerializationUtils.Serialize(set));
	}
}
```

