TITLE: Updating kendoDatePicker Date Format in HTML5 MVC Report Viewer
DESCRIPTION: This script modifies the date format of the kendoDatePicker within the ReportViewer's UpdateUi event to the specified format. It uses a flag to ensure the date format change occurs only once during the viewer's lifecycle. Dependencies include jQuery and Kendo UI libraries. Key parameter: dateFormat, which defines the desired date format. Input is the existing date format in the viewer, output is the updated format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/knowledge-base/how-to-change-report-parameter-date-format-in-html5-mvc-report-viewer.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: HTML
CODE:
```
<script>
	var dateUpdated = false;// Flag to indicate that date format has been set

	function setDateFormat(dateFormat) {
		var datepicker = $("#reportViewer1").find("[data-role='datepicker']");
		if (datepicker.length > 0) {
			dateUpdated = true;

			for (var i = 0; i < datepicker.length; i += 1) {
				var dp = $(datepicker[i]).data("kendoDatePicker");
				var currentFormat = dp.options.format;
				var oldValue = dp.value();

				dp.options.format = dateFormat;
				dp.value(oldValue);
			}
		}
	}

	function onUpdateUi() {
		// Skip if date format already set
		if (!dateUpdated) {
			setDateFormat("dd/MM/yyyy");//SPECIFY THE DATE FORMAT HERE
		}
	}
</script>
```

