TITLE: Binding ObjectDataSource to SqlDataAdapter in VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This VB.NET code snippet shows how to create a SqlDataAdapter, set up an ObjectDataSource to use it, and configure a report with a calculated field. It also demonstrates how to preview the report in a Windows Forms Report Viewer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-source-components/objectdatasource-component/bind-to-data-adapter.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
Public Sub BindToDataAdapter()
    Dim report As New Report()
    Dim detail As New DetailSection()
    report.Items.Add(detail)

    ' Create the ObjectDataSource component
    Dim objectDataSource As New Telerik.Reporting.ObjectDataSource()

    Dim sqlConnection As New SqlConnection("connection string")
    Dim sqlDataAdapter As New SqlDataAdapter("SELECT * FROM Employees", sqlConnection)

    ' Specify the data adapter
    objectDataSource.DataSource = sqlDataAdapter
    objectDataSource.DataMember = "Table"

    ' Add a calculated field
    Dim calculatedField As New Telerik.Reporting.CalculatedField()
    calculatedField.Name = "FullName"
    calculatedField.Expression = "FirstName + \" \" + LastName"
    objectDataSource.CalculatedFields.Add(calculatedField)

    ' Set the data source of the report
    report.DataSource = objectDataSource

    ' Add a TextBox item to the detail section to display the calculated field
    Dim textBox As New Telerik.Reporting.TextBox()
    textBox.Size = New SizeU(Unit.Inch(5), Unit.Inch(1))
    textBox.Name = "textBox"
    textBox.Value = "= Fields.FullName"
    detail.Items.Add(textBox)

    ' Preview the report
    Dim reportProcessor As New ReportProcessor()
    Dim viewer As New Telerik.ReportViewer.WinForms.ReportViewer()
    viewer.ReportSource = New Telerik.Reporting.InstanceReportSource() With {.ReportDocument = report}
    viewer.RefreshReport()
    viewer.ShowDialog()
End Sub
```

