TITLE: Adding a Group to Table Data Item Programmatically in VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to programmatically add a new group to a Table data item in VB.NET. It creates a new RowGroup called 'regionRowGroup' that groups by the Region field, adds sorting by the Region field in ascending order, and adds the group to the Table's RowGroups collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-items/grouping-data/how-to-add-groups-to-table-item-and-crosstab-item.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
Public Sub AddNewGroup()
    'create a group that groups by the Region field.
    Dim regionRowGroup As New Telerik.Reporting.TableGroup()
    regionRowGroup.Name = "regionRowGroup"
    'Specify the grouping expression
    regionRowGroup.Groupings.Add(New Telerik.Reporting.Grouping("=Fields.Region"))
    'Specify the sort expression for the group
    regionRowGroup.Sortings.Add(New Telerik.Reporting.Sorting("=Fields.Region", Telerik.Reporting.SortDirection.Asc))

    'add the region group to the table's RowGroups collection
    Me.table1.RowGroups.Add(regionRowGroup)
End Sub
```

