TITLE: Handling interactiveActionExecuting Event in HTML5 Report Viewer (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to handle the interactiveActionExecuting event in the Telerik HTML5 Report Viewer. It shows how to intercept and potentially cancel a 'navigateToReport' action by prompting the user for confirmation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/embedding-reports/display-reports-in-applications/web-application/html5-report-viewer/api-reference/reportviewer/events/interactiveactionexecuting(e,-args).md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// $(handler) is jQuery's shorthand for $(document).ready(handler)
$(function () {
	$("#reportViewer1").telerik_ReportViewer({
		serviceUrl: "api/reports/",
		reportSource: {
			report: "Telerik.Reporting.Examples.CSharp.ProductSales, CSharp.ReportLibrary"
		},
		interactiveActionExecuting: function(e, args) {
			if (args.action.Type === 'navigateToReport') {
				args.cancel = !confirm("You are about to navigate to report "+args.action.Value.Report + ".\r\n\nContinue?");
			}
		}
	});
});
```

