TITLE: Creating User Function for Data Type Parsing in C#
DESCRIPTION: Custom User Function class that converts string values to integers when possible, otherwise returns the original string. This helps avoid Excel formatting warnings by ensuring proper data types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/knowledge-base/number-in-the-cell-is-formatted-as-text-or-preceded-by-an-apostrophe.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public static class ReturnTypeClass
{
    public static object ParseString(string str)
    {
        Int32 intValue;
        if (Int32.TryParse(str, out intValue))
            return intValue;
        else return str;
    }
}
```

