TITLE: Adding a Group to Table Data Item Programmatically in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to programmatically add a new group to a Table data item in C#. It creates a new RowGroup called 'regionRowGroup' that groups by the Region field, adds sorting by the Region field in ascending order, and adds the group to the Table's RowGroups collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-items/grouping-data/how-to-add-groups-to-table-item-and-crosstab-item.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
public void AddNewGroup()
{
    //create a group that groups by the Region field.
    Telerik.Reporting.TableGroup regionRowGroup = new Telerik.Reporting.TableGroup();
    regionRowGroup.Name = "regionRowGroup";
    //Specify the grouping expression
    regionRowGroup.Groupings.Add(new Telerik.Reporting.Grouping("=Fields.Region"));
    //Specify the sort expression for the group
    regionRowGroup.Sortings.Add(new Telerik.Reporting.Sorting("=Fields.Region", Telerik.Reporting.SortDirection.Asc));

    //add the region group to the table's RowGroups collection
    this.table1.RowGroups.Add(regionRowGroup);
}
```

