TITLE: Binding ObjectDataSource to DataTable in VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This VB.NET code snippet demonstrates how to create a DataTable, add a calculated field, configure an ObjectDataSource, and set up a report to use it. It also shows how to preview the report in a Windows Forms Report Viewer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/designing-reports/connecting-to-data/data-source-components/objectdatasource-component/bind-to-data-table.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
Public Sub HowToBindToDataTable()
    Dim dt As New DataTable()
    dt.Columns.Add("ProductID", GetType(Integer))
    dt.Columns.Add("ProductName", GetType(String))
    dt.Columns.Add("UnitPrice", GetType(Decimal))
    dt.Columns.Add("UnitsInStock", GetType(Int16))
    dt.Rows.Add(1, "Chai", 18.0, 39)
    dt.Rows.Add(2, "Chang", 19.0, 17)
    dt.Rows.Add(3, "Aniseed Syrup", 10.0, 13)

    Dim calcColumn As New DataColumn("Total")
    calcColumn.DataType = GetType(Decimal)
    calcColumn.Expression = "UnitPrice * UnitsInStock"
    dt.Columns.Add(calcColumn)

    Dim objectDataSource As New ObjectDataSource()
    objectDataSource.DataSource = dt

    Dim report As New Report()
    report.DataSource = objectDataSource

    Dim reportProcessor As New ReportProcessor()
    Dim result As RenderingResult = reportProcessor.RenderReport("PDF", report, Nothing)

    System.IO.File.WriteAllBytes("report.pdf", result.DocumentBytes)
End Sub
```

