TITLE: Exporting to Multi-Document Formats in VB.NET using Telerik Reporting
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates exporting a report to multi-document formats using VB.NET. It shows how to render a report to JPEG images using the CreateStream callback with device information for controlling image quality and resolution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/embedding-reports/generate-reports-locally.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: VB.NET
CODE:
```
' Exporting to image format:
Dim rs As New InstanceReportSource()
rs.ReportDocument = New Report1()

Dim reportProcessor As New ReportProcessor()

' An instance of the Hashtable class to create a deviceInfo.
Dim deviceInfo As New System.Collections.Hashtable()

' Setting the DPI.
deviceInfo.Add("DpiX", "300")
deviceInfo.Add("DpiY", "300")

' Setting the image quality. The quality must be between 0 and 100.
deviceInfo.Add("OutputFormat", "JPEG")
deviceInfo.Add("JpegQuality", "80")

reportProcessor.RenderReport("IMAGE", rs, deviceInfo, createStreamCallback, Nothing)

Private Shared Function createStreamCallback(name As String, extension As String, encoding As String, mimeType As String, willSeek As Boolean) As MemoryStream
    ' We only need to care about the extension, a more general implementation would
    ' pay attention to name, encoding, and mimeType as well.
    Dim fileName As String = "" + Guid.NewGuid().ToString() + "." + extension.Replace(".", "")

    If File.Exists(fileName) Then
        File.Delete(fileName)
    End If

    Dim stream As New MemoryStream()

    Return stream
End Function
```

