TITLE: Creating Custom Shape Class in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a custom shape by inheriting from the ShapeBase class and defining a set of points to form the shape.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/report-items/shape.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
public class CustomShape : ShapeBase
{
    public CustomShape()
    {
    }

    public override PointF[][] GetPoints()
    {
        return new PointF[][] {
            new PointF[] {
                new PointF(0, 0),
                new PointF(1, 0),
                new PointF(1, 1),
                new PointF(0, 1)
            }
        };
    }
}
```

