TITLE: Adding Text Watermark Programmatically in C# and VB.NET
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to programmatically add a text watermark to a report by creating a TextWatermark instance, setting its properties such as Text, Font, Color, Opacity, and Position, and adding it to the report's PageSettings.Watermarks collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/reporting-docs.git/blob/master/styling/rendering-and-paging/watermarks.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
Report report = new Report();

// Create a new TextWatermark
TextWatermark textWatermark = new TextWatermark();

// Set the properties
textWatermark.Text = "Draft";
textWatermark.Font = new Drawing.TypedFont("Arial", Drawing.TypedFontStyle.Bold, Drawing.Unit.Point(60));
textWatermark.Color = Drawing.Color.FromArgb(50, Drawing.Color.Gray);
textWatermark.Opacity = 0.2;
textWatermark.Position = WatermarkPosition.Front;
textWatermark.Orientation = WatermarkOrientation.Diagonal;
textWatermark.PrintOnFirstPage = true;
textWatermark.PrintOnLastPage = true;

// Add the watermark to the Watermarks collection
report.PageSettings.Watermarks.Add(textWatermark);
```

